The continuous-time Markov model (CTMM) is more appropriate for non-uniform observation times, although for two-state data, the DTMM and CTMM methods may produce similar results for naturally discretized data (e.g. prespecified time points based on clinical trial designs) [10]. In this method, the influence of the previous state on the probability of the current state typically decreases with increasing time between observations [16–18].\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
