				\begin{document}$$p10$$\end{document}p10) was 25.4%. This difference may reflect the natural decline in antibody levels due to a diminished immune response or immune tolerance, treatment interventions (such as immunosuppressive therapies), or variability in sensitivity and specificity in assays used to detect ADA [37].
